About the Department

The Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade (DFAT) advances Australia's international interests by strengthening security, expanding trade and investment, and supporting sustainable development. DFAT works to protect Australia's global interests, contribute to regional and international stability, and promote Australia's values and prosperity worldwide.

Develop other deliverables as required for emerging needs.

Demonstrated experience as a business analyst working on significant ICT projects, ideally within Australian government environments.
Ability to define clear, measurable acceptance criteria to ensure features and functions meet business requirements and are fit for purpose.
Strong communication skills and the ability to engage with stakeholders at all levels.
High level of initiative and the ability to work independently.

Australian citizens with an NV1 Australian Government security clearance mandatory, and the ability to obtain an NV2

Overview of the Role

We are seeking an experienced Senior Power BI Developer to design, build, and optimise enterprise-grade analytics and reporting solutions for complex client environments. You will work closely with data engineers, product teams, and senior stakeholders to translate business questions into clear, high-impact insights.

This role is hands-on and delivery-focused, suited to someone who enjoys owning analytics outcomes end-to-end, from data modelling through to executive-ready dashboards.

Australian work rights are required for this position.

Key Responsibilities

Design and develop scalable Power BI dashboards and reports for enterprise and regulated environments

Work directly with stakeholders to define KPIs, reporting requirements, and analytical outcomes

Contribute to analytics standards, patterns, and best practices across engagements
